begin
select [id], [run_id], [test], [expected], [actual], [executed_at], [result] from [test].[result] where [run_id] = @@run_id;
declare @failed int = ( select count(1) from [test].[result] where result = 'FAILED' and [run_id] = @@run_id )
if (@failed > 0) begin declare @msg varchar(50) = FORMATMESSAGE( '%i or more tests failed.', @failed); throw 60000, @msg, 1; end
end
